<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN1057B" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Display Guides</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN1057F" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Displays or hides guides that you can use to align objects on a page.</paragraph>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN10582" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Snap to Guides</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN10586" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW">Automatically aligns objects to vertical and horizontal guides. To override this feature, hold down the <switchinline select="sys"><caseinline select="MAC">Control key 
</caseinline><defaultinline>Ctrl key when you drag an object.</defaultinline></switchinline>.<comment>UFI: test it! copied from shared\01\grid.xhp</comment></paragraph><comment>UFI: removed double help id</comment>
<paragraph role="heading" id="par_idN105C6" xml-lang="en-US" level="2" l10n="NEW">Guides to Front</paragraph>
<paragraph role="paragraph" id="par_idN105CA" xml-lang="en-US" l10n="NEW"><ahelp hid=".">Displays the guides in front of the objects on the slide or page.</ahelp></paragraph>
